SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 5116
A bill to amend 1972 PA 382, entitled
"Traxler-McCauley-Law-Bowman bingo act,"
by amending section 41 (MCL 432.141), as added by 2019 PA 159.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 41. (1) A millionaire party licensee shall ensure that an
2 event conducted under the license is conducted in compliance with
3 this act and the rules promulgated under this act.
4 (2) A millionaire party licensee shall post the license so
5 that it is conspicuously visible at the location where the event is
6 being conducted at all times during the event.
7 (3) A millionaire party licensee shall not conduct gaming
8 under the license anywhere outside of the demarcated area approved
9 by the executive director.
THS H04192'25 (H-1) 86c9mj

2
1 (4) A millionaire party licensee shall ensure that access to
2 the demarcated area is controlled.
3 (5) A millionaire party licensee shall not allow an individual
4 who is less than 18 years old of age to enter the demarcated area
5 when gaming is being conducted there.
6 (6) If alcoholic beverages are served at an event, an
7 individual in the demarcated area who is 18 years old of age or
8 older but less than 21 years old of age must be identified by
9 wearing a mark indicating that a member or agent of the millionaire
10 party licensee has verified the individual's age and
11 identification.
12 (7) A millionaire party licensee shall not receive more than
13 $20,000.00 $35,000.00 in exchange for imitation money or chips on
14 any day under the license. However, if the licensee conducts the
15 millionaire party without using dealers from a supplier and owns
16 the location at which the millionaire party is held and if the
17 license is for fewer than 4 days of gaming, the daily limit under
18 this subsection is determined by dividing $80,000.00 $140,000.00 by
19 the number of days of gaming allowed under the license.
20 (8) A millionaire party licensee may conduct a charity game as
21 provided in section 7b and may conduct a numeral game as provided
22 in section 7c. If a millionaire party licensee conducts a charity
23 game or a numeral game, the executive director has sole enforcement
24 and supervision authority over the conduct of the game.
